{
  "text": "With regards to the duration of treatment, we advise treatment until age 12 years in individuals with untreated phenylalanine concentrations between 360 \u03bcmol/L and Review 600 \u03bcmol/L, providing blood phenylalanine remains less than 600 \u03bcmol/L without treatment afterwards. We suggest this duration because of scarce and inconsistent evidence and the necessity for good metabolic control to retain cognitive function, especially during the fi rst 12 years of life. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] In untreated women with phenylalanine concentrations of more than 360 \u03bcmol/L, treatment is also required preconception and during pregnancy with the aim of reducing phenylalanine concentrations to less than 360 \u03bcmol/L.",
